cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the task of depth estimation from a single RGB image using unsupervised learning. The approach is based on depth from defocus cues, which is a computer vision technique related to image processing and graphics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel Point Spread Function convolutional layer, which is a deep learning technique, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on five common datasets for depth estimation and lightfield images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics).
